  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "F&B Restaurant Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Company Overview</strong></p><p>Family run business in providing fresh Chinese seafood cuisine to the local community.</p><p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Lead restaurant operations to deliver exceptional customer experiences and achieve sales targets through strategic staff management, operational oversight, and adherence to hygiene and safety standards.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead the recruitment process by screening, interviewing, hiring, and training restaurant staff to build a skilled and motivated team</li><li>Develop and manage staff work schedules to optimize operational efficiency and coverage</li><li>Conduct regular inspections of the kitchen to ensure compliance with hygiene and sanitation standards, maintaining a safe food preparation environment</li><li>Monitor inventory levels and coordinate timely restocking of food supplies and restaurant essentials to support uninterrupted service</li><li>Design and implement strategies to enhance staff morale, motivation, and engagement, fostering a positive workplace culture</li><li>Develop and execute sales strategies tailored to customer profiles to meet and exceed revenue targets</li><li>Plan, organize, and direct daily restaurant operations to ensure smooth and efficient service delivery</li><li>Monitor cash flow and manage settlement of outstanding bills to maintain financial accuracy and accountability</li><li>Analyze customer feedback from surveys to identify service improvement opportunities and implement corrective actions</li><li>Resolve customer complaints professionally to maintain high customer satisfaction and loyalty</li><li>Maintain equipment by conducting regular inspections and coordinating maintenance to ensure operational reliability</li><li>Enforce compliance with food and beverage safety and hygiene policies and procedures to uphold regulatory standards</li><li>Collaborate effectively as a diligent team player passionate about food and beverage operations</li><li>Communicate clearly and lead teams to achieve operational goals in a fast-paced environment</li><li>Manage multiple tasks simultaneously while maintaining quality and efficiency under pressure</li></ul><p>Working Hours</p><ul><li>6 days per week, up to 44 hours per week</li><li>Weekday shifts: 11am-3pm, 5:30pm-10:30pm</li><li>Weekend shifts: 10:30am-3pm, 5pm-11pm</li><li>Off on Tuesday</li></ul><ul><li>Interested applicants please WhatsApp to 80493249 (please note we do not entertain calls)</li></ul>",
